  "_about": "Anatomically Programmed Radiography (APR) chart. Selecting a protocol sets the technique (kVp / mAs), anti-scatter grid, and display LUT for that projection. Grouped body part -> region -> projection. kVp/mAs follow typical adult DR technique charts: distal extremities 50-65 kVp no grid; proximal limb + skull/spine/abdomen/pelvis 70-90 kVp with grid; chest high-kVp 110-125 kVp with grid. Values are teaching approximations, not a substitute for a facility chart.",
